{
  "answer": "**The *Vr̥haspatitattva* (Vrhaspati's treatise on reality), attributed to Bṛhaspati, opens with a dialogue between Lord Śiva and Vṛhaspati in which the foundational principles (*tattvas*) of existence are expounded.**[^1]\n\nThe core definition appears early, in verses 6–7 of Chapter 1. The supreme *tattva* (reality) is declared twofold: *cetana* (the Conscious Principle) and *acetana* (the Unconscious Principle). These pervade all other *tattvas*, are subtle, and require discernment.[^2]\n\n*Cetana* is intrinsically aware, self-knowing, eternal, and unobscured by ignorance or forgetting—like a luminous consciousness. *Acetana*, by contrast, lacks awareness entirely, exemplified by inert matter such as stone.[^3] **Their relationship is generative: when *cetana* and *acetana* unite (*atĕmu pvekaṅ cetana lavan acetana*), they produce the full hierarchy of *tattvas* (principles of reality), beginning with *pradhānatattva* (primordial nature) and descending through *triguṇa* (three qualities), intellect (*buddhi*), ego (*ahaṅkāra*), senses, and the five gross elements (*pañcamahābhūta*).** This union underlies manifestation, binding consciousness within unconscious matter and initiating the cycle of *saṃsāra* (rebirth). Pure *cetana* (*Śiva*-tattvas) remains transcendent, while *acetana* (*māyā*-tattvas) veils it, causing limitation until liberation (*mokṣa*).\n\nLater sections elaborate: *acetana* (*mala*, impurity) stains *cetana*, obscuring its omniscience and omnipotence, much like unconsciousness causes forgetting in sleep.[^4] Full realization dissolves this, restoring unity.\n\n[^1]: *Vr̥haspatitattva*, Ch. 1 [Chapter](/works/unknown-vrhaspatitattva-b60b28/01/translation/).\n\n[^2]: *Vr̥haspatitattva*, Ch. 1 [paragraphs](/works/unknown-vrhaspatitattva-b60b28/01/translation/#p-04d69c).\n\n[^3]: *Vr̥haspatitattva*, Ch. 1 [paragraphs](/works/unknown-vrhaspatitattva-b60b28/01/translation/#p-c31df3).\n\n[^4]: *Vr̥haspatitattva*, Ch. 1 [paragraphs](/works/unknown-vrhaspatitattva-b60b28/01/translation/#p-643885).",
